-- HSBC Middle East raises $400 mln through five-year bond sale 
-- By Archana Narayanan
-- Wed Sep 24, 2014 02:33AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, Sept 23 (Reuters) - HSBC Bank Middle East raised $400 million in a five-year bond issue late on Tuesday at a spread of 85 basis points over mid-swaps, a document from the bank said.

The lender had said earlier on Tuesday it was set to raise a minimum of $300 million from the bond sale at the tighter end of its initial guidance of between 85 bps and 90 bps over the benchmark. [ID:nL6N0RO0NV] The issue, arranged solely by HSBC <HSBA.L>, priced at a coupon of 2.75 percent, with a reoffer price of 99.824.